\"wrap\">(</span><span class=\"dtxt\">in <span class=\"ndv\">cricket</span></span><span class=\"wrap\">)</span></span> <span class=\"def\" htag=\"span\" hclass=\"def\">the act of ending an <span class=\"ndv\">innings</span> before all your players have <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/bat_2#bat_sng_13\" title=\"batted definition\"><span class=\"ndv\">batted</span></a></span><ul class=\"examples\" hclass=\"examples\" htag=\"ul\"><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"x\">After England's declaration at 379 for 6, they overwhelmed their hapless opponents.</span></li></ul>      </li><div class=\"collapse\" hclass=\"collapse\" htag=\"div\"><span class=\"unbox\" id=\"declaration_unbox_2\" unbox=\"wordorigin\"><span class=\"box_title\">Word Origin</span><span class=\"body\"><span class=\"p\">late Middle English: from Latin <span class=\"ei\">declaratio(n-)</span>, from <span class=\"ei\">declarare</span> ‘make quite clear’, from <span class=\"ei\">de-</span> ‘thoroughly’ + <span class=\"ei\">clarare</span> ‘make clear’.</span></span></span></div></ol><span class=\"dictlink-g\"><span class=\"dictlink\">See <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/american_english/declaration\" title=\" definition in American English\n \"><span class=\"xh\">declaration</span></a> in the Oxford Advanced American Dictionary</span><span class=\"dictlink\">See <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/academic/declaration\" title=\" definition in Academic English\n \"><span class=\"xh\">declaration</span></a> in the Oxford Learner's Dictionary of Academic English</span></span><div class=\"pron-link\">Check pronunciation:\n                        <a href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/pronunciation/english/declaration\">declaration</a></div></div>\n","matches":["the Balfour Declaration","the Declaration of Independence noun","the Downing Street Declaration"